Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%labels
Author linux-support-bot
Description Container prepared for “system snapshot” exercise.  Includes Python 3, pytest, and required system utilities.

%post
    set -e

    echo "Updating package lists..."
    apt-get update -y

    echo "Installing required Debian/Ubuntu packages..."
    # iproute2 supplies the `ss` command; python3 is already present but
    # install pip so we can add pytest.
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        iproute2 \
        python3-pip

    echo "Installing pytest via pip..."
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    echo "Creating /home/user with liberal permissions..."
    mkdir -p /home/user
    # Make it writable for any UID that might run inside the container.
    chmod 0777 /home/user

    echo "Cleaning up apt caches..."
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

%environment
    chmod 755 /home/user

    # Ensure pip-installed executables are on the PATH
    export PATH="$PATH:/usr/local/bin"

%runscript
    # Default action: start an interactive shell
    exec /bin/bash "$@"

%help
This container provides the environment required for the “system snapshot”
task.  It includes:
  • Python 3 (>=3.10)
  • pytest
  • Core GNU utilities plus iproute2 (for the `ss` command)

The home directory /home/user exists and is writable.  The diagnostics
artefacts that the learner must create are purposefully **not** present.